A History of Self-Harm in Britain - A Genealogy of Cutting and Overdosing - 1st Edition - 2015th Edition (2016).pdf Gooner

Publisher: Palgrave Macmillan; 1st ed. 2015 edition (February 16, 2016)
Language: English
ISBN-10: 1137547731
ISBN-13: 978-1137547736

This book is open access under a CC BY license and charts the rise and fall of various self-harming behaviours in twentieth-century Britain. It puts self-cutting and overdosing into historical perspective, linking them to the huge changes that occur in mental and physical healthcare, social work and wider politics
